{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idcc8116b5-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s60124"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"60124"},"text":"§ 60124.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Biennial reports","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idcc8116b6-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s60124/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Submission and Contents","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"Not later than ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1997-08-15"},"text":"August 15, 1997","children":[],"tail":", and every 2 years thereafter, the Secretary of Transportation shall submit to Congress a report on carrying out this chapter for the 2 immediately preceding calendar years for gas and a report on carrying out this chapter for such period for hazardous liquid. Each report shall include the following information about the prior year for gas or hazardous liquid, as appropriate:"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idcc8116b7-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s60124/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a thorough compilation of the leak repairs, accidents, and casualties and a statement of cause when investigated and established by the National Transportation Safety Board.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idcc8116b8-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s60124/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a list of applicable pipeline safety standards prescribed under this chapter including identification of standards prescribed during the year.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idcc8116b9-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s60124/a/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a summary of the reasons for each waiver granted under section 60118(c) and (d) of this title.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idcc8116ba-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s60124/a/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" an evaluation of the degree of compliance with applicable safety standards, including a list of enforcement actions and compromises of alleged violations by location and company name.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idcc8116bb-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s60124/a/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a summary of outstanding problems in carrying out this chapter, in order of priority.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idcc8116bc-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s60124/a/6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"6"},"text":"(6)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" an analysis and evaluation of—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idcc8116bd-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s60124/a/6/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" research activities, including their policy implications, completed as a result of the United States Government and private sponsorship;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idcc8116be-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s60124/a/6/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" technological progress in safety achieved; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idcc8116bf-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s60124/a/6/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a summary of each research and development project carried out with Federal and non-Federal entities pursuant to section 12 of the Pipeline Safety Improvement Act of 2002 and a review of how the project affects safety.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idcc8116c0-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s60124/a/7"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"7"},"text":"(7)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a list, with a brief statement of the issues, of completed or pending judicial actions under this chapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idcc8116c1-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s60124/a/8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"8"},"text":"(8)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the extent to which technical information was distributed to the scientific community and consumer-oriented information was made available to the public.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idcc8116c2-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70","identifier":"/us/usc/t49/s60124/a/9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","a